The article is a Presidential Proclamation by Barack Obama declaring September 17, 2010, as National POW/MIA Recognition Day. The proclamation pays tribute to American servicemembers who never returned home from combat, those who suffered as prisoners of war, and all servicemembers who defended American lives and liberties. The proclamation emphasizes the commitment to accounting for missing members of the Armed Forces and bringing them home. It mentions the efforts of the Department of Defense to gather information about missing individuals from various conflicts. The article also mentions that on September 17, 2010, the black and white flag honoring prisoners of war and the missing in action will be flown over various locations across the country. The proclamation urges all Americans to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.